Classes:

Object-Oriented programming(oop) is one of the most effective approaches to writing 
software. In object-Oriented programming, you write classes that represent real-world
things and situations, and you create object based on these classes. When you write a 
class, you define the general behavior that a whole category of objects can have..

Making an object from class is called instantiation. and we work with instance of a class.

Capitalized names refer to classes in Python. There are no paranthesis in the class definition,
because we are creating these classes from scratch.We then write a docstring what this class does.

The _init_() method:
A function thats part of a class is a method. 
Everything we learned about the function applies to methods.

The _int_() method is a special method that python runs automatically
whenever we create a new instance based on the class


#Modifying attribute values:
We can change attriute values in three ways:
1. Directly through an instance.
2. Set the value through a method.
3. Increment the value through a method.


#inheritence:
When we create a child class, the parent class must be part of he current file and must appeat before the child class in the file. We then define the child class the name of the parent class must be included in parantheses in the defination of a child class

